description: Harrogate hand rock-bottom Carlisle's League Two survival hopes a major blow as they net a stoppage-time winner.
title: Harrogate Town 1-0 Carlisle United
title_page: Harrogate Town 1-0 Carlisle United - BBC Sport
maintext:
Harrogate Town are unbeaten across their seven Football League games against Carlisle United (W4 D3), scoring at least once in each of those matches.
Carlisle United have failed to win any of their last eight away league games against sides from Yorkshire (D2 L6), since a 1-0 win over Bradford City in December 2020.
Harrogate have won each of their last two home league games and could win three in succession for the first time since April 2024.
Carlisle will be looking to win successive away league games for the first time since March 2023 after beating Barrow 1-0 in their last away fixture.
